---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro'; import PageHero from '../components/PageHero.astro'; import ColourSwatch from '../components/ColourSwatch.astro';
---
<BaseLayout title="Colours — Leicester Space Week brand"><PageHero eyebrow="Colour system" title="A night sky with a beacon." intro="Our palette pairs a deep, credible night sky with one warm signature accent. It is practical, distinctive and built for accessible communication." /><section class="section"><div class="shell"><div class="colour-grid"><ColourSwatch name="Orbit Navy" hex="#0B1026" text="Primary field"/><ColourSwatch name="Beacon Amber" hex="#E2672A" kind="paper" text="Signature accent"/><ColourSwatch name="Civic Violet" hex="#5B2A86" text="Partners & community"/><ColourSwatch name="Steel Silver" hex="#C9CED6" kind="paper" text="Lines & structure"/><ColourSwatch name="Paper White" hex="#F4F2ED" kind="paper" text="Light canvas"/><ColourSwatch name="Ink" hex="#14172B" text="Reading text"/></div></div></section><section class="section" style="background:#fff"><div class="shell"><div class="section-head"><p class="eyebrow">Colour usage</p><h2>Make contrast do the work.</h2><p>Orbit Navy is our dominant field; Beacon Amber is deliberately scarce and should lead attention, not fill a page. Keep body copy in Ink on Paper White wherever possible.</p></div><div class="usage"><article class="usage-panel do"><span class="check">✓</span><h3>Primary pairings</h3><p>Paper White on Orbit Navy, Ink on Paper White, and Paper White on Civic Violet form the core accessible combinations.</p></article><article class="usage-panel dont"><span class="cross">×</span><h3>Avoid low contrast</h3><p>Do not set body copy in Steel Silver, or use Beacon Amber for small text on light backgrounds.</p></article></div></div></section></BaseLayout>
